@jeremie1112 
- Since `org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-parent` also has this problem, I think it is better to wait for the official release of spring-boot `2.7.0` to deal with this problem. A simple solution is mentioned at https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-boot/issues/29034 . The goal of this PR should be repositioned to focus on more pressing issues.
- Reference https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-starter-parent/2.6.4 .

> Hi @SirMin, thank you for your great contribution. Can we add an SPI interface for database dialects, as the type conversion mechanism may not be the same for different databases.

@strongduanmu  TypeHandlerFactory save data structure of JDBC type - > whether it is signed - > TypeHandler list (by prioritization).
Can define high priority typehandlers with the same JDBC type and signs to customize the conversion of different database types by judging the resultset's type.

@pparthenhs 
Very concise and accurate PR, thanks for your work.
I'll merge it after the CI is successful.
